 &lt;h1 id=&#34;windows-ad-auto-pentest-tool&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#windows-ad-auto-pentest-tool&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Windows AD Auto Pentest Tool&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduce&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#introduce&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Introduce&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img data-src=&#34;/self_develop/winAD-APT/0.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
WinAD-APT, is the windwos active directory auto pentesting tool&#39;s abbreviation. When I do some windows activate pentesing research, I found that the tools for windows active directory pentesting is complex, so I write this tool to integrated the tools which is useful for all the usual payload and exploit, and provide a ui website so make ADpentesting more easily.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This tool is made of python streamlit, and mainly use linux command to do the pentesting, all the things we need to do is to full in the blanks like username and password, and click the button to exploit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This tool is still being developed, it is recommand to add your command into this tool and customize your own tool&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The tool is uploaded to github: &lt;span class=&#34;exturl&#34; data-url=&#34;aHR0cHM6Ly9naXRodWIuY29tL3BocmlzbS9XaW5BRC1BUFQ=&#34;&gt;winAD-APT&lt;/span&gt; , it is welcome to download and test it,  if you think the project is useful, a star is appreciated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;usage&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#usage&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Usage&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you run the &lt;span class=&#34;exturl&#34; data-url=&#34;aHR0cDovL1N0YXJ0LnB5&#34;&gt;Start.py&lt;/span&gt; file in the winAD-APT, your brower will automatically stared and lead you to the start page, you can set your target ip here&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img data-src=&#34;/self_develop/winAD-APT/1.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The winAD-APT is made of 7 sub-parts:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nmap&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;InfoGather&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lateralpenetration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PermissionSploit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CrackHash&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;History&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ViewFile&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Nmap,  you can start your nmap scan and custom the parameters in nmap, default is &amp;quot;-sV -sC -A -Pn -T4&amp;quot;, you can set your target domain here, and the open port information is essential for the lateral information gather.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img data-src=&#34;/self_develop/winAD-APT/7.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In InfoGather, you can use different tools like rpcclient, smbclient etc. to gather information according to the open port the nmap showed, you need to set your target ip and target domian before use this part of tools&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img data-src=&#34;/self_develop/winAD-APT/2.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Lateralpenetration, you can use common lateral pentetrstion tools like bloodhound, powerview or ldapmonitor, you can set the username and credentials you get in InforGather part, and all the credentails are stored by fault.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img data-src=&#34;/self_develop/winAD-APT/3.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In PermissionSploit, this part is mainly accomplished by winrm, and use windows commad instead of linux command, so there&#39;s not much auto pentesting tool here, there&#39;s some tips and command listed here for usage&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img data-src=&#34;/self_develop/winAD-APT/6.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In CrackHash, you can paste your password hash here and use either hashcat ot john to crack the hash.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img data-src=&#34;/self_develop/winAD-APT/4.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In History, you can see all the history input and output here, so there&#39;s no need to clear your command line and lose some important information&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img data-src=&#34;/self_develop/winAD-APT/8.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In ViewFile, you can view and edit the user and password file stored on your system, and save them from the ui, you can also use notes to take notes whenever you like, please do not forget to pres the save button!&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img data-src=&#34;/self_develop/winAD-APT/5.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
